        [
          "Ex-Sabbat Pander who has left the sect in the wake of the civil war and been an independent and is joining the Camarilla for his own reasons.."
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Zip Manning. There was a time, years ago, when that name would bring up memories of panicked terror, splattering blood and the nightmarish sound of a chainsaw tearing through flesh. But now, all those that remembered were dead. Enemies and allies both, long since turned to ash.\nThe well earned reputation faded away and forgotten.\n        He really didn’t mind too much.\n\n        Embraced in 1993 as a disposable soldier for the Sword of Caine, the man that would become Zip Manning exceeded all expectations of brutality and combat effectiveness from the moment he burst  from a shallow grave and tore open the throat of the fool that had checked the recently disturbed earth, up until the day the last member of his original pack died in the burst of an incendiary grenade. For nearly twenty years, he traveled the southwest with his pack as a prized Executioner, but as the years grew and his packmates died, his loyalty to the sect faded. It had taken him years to understand why he never felt the bliss his friends described when they spoke of the Vaulderie. Some defect of his embrace had rendered him immune to the lesser bonds, even if he wanted them. But despite that flaw, his friends accepted him and helped him hide the fact from the Sabbat at large. Twisted though it was, the family they provided was a delight compared to the one he’d known as a mortal and his loyalty was theirs to command. Once they were gone though… well. He didn’t really have a reason to stay. It was during the Nights of Turmoil that he lost the last members of his pack. The lone survivor of a failed war party, he took the opportunity to disappear and search for a new purpose in unlife."
        ],
